issues.body:
**Bug description**

Integrate Claude OpenAI compatiable API with spring-ai-openai-spring-boot-starter, and chat with ai, NPE occurs:
```
java.lang.NullPointerException: null
	at java.base/java.util.Objects.requireNonNull(Objects.java:233) ~[na:na]
	at java.base/java.util.ImmutableCollections$MapN.<init>(ImmutableCollections.java:1193) ~[na:na]
	at java.base/java.util.Map.of(Map.java:1457) ~[na:na]
	at org.springframework.ai.openai.OpenAiChatModel.lambda$internalCall$2(OpenAiChatModel.java:291) ~[spring-ai-openai-1.0.0-M6.jar:1.0.0-M6]
```

**Environment**
spring-ai 1.0.0-M7
jdk 17

**Steps to reproduce**

1. config:

```
spring:
  main:
    web-application-type: none
  ai:
    openai:
      base-url: ${CLAUDE_BASE_URL}
      api-key: ${CLAUDE_API_KEY}
      chat:
        options:
          model: claude-3-7-sonnet-20250219
```

2. app:

```
@SpringBootApplication
public class Application {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        SpringApplication.run(Application.class, args);
    }

    @Bean
    CommandLineRunner cli(ChatClient.Builder builder) {
        return args -> {
            var chat = builder
                    .defaultAdvisors(new MessageChatMemoryAdvisor(new InMemoryChatMemory()))
                    .build();

            var scanner = new Scanner(System.in);
            System.out.println("\nLet's chat!");
            while (true) {
                System.out.print("\nUSER: ");
                System.out.println("ASSISTANT: " + chat.prompt(scanner.nextLine()).call().content());
            }
        };
    }

}
```

3. chat with ai

**Expected behavior**

I think spring-ai-openai-spring-boot-starter should be compatiable with Claude OpenAI compatiable API.

After some investigation, I found that the Claude API response format is:

```json
{
   "id":"9c09e295-0bca-499e-8373-98833861ba59",
   "model":"claude-3-7-sonnet-20250219",
   "choices":[
      {
         "message":{
            "role":"assistant",
            "content":"Hello! How can I assist you today? I'm here to help with any questions or tasks you might have."
         },
         "finish_reason":"stop"
      }
   ],
   "created":1744684923,
   "object":"chat.completion",
   "usage":{
      "prompt_tokens":15,
      "completion_tokens":26,
      "total_tokens":41
   }
}
```
 `index` attribute in `choices` field value is missing, which cause NPE in spring-ai. I'm not sure if `index` attribute can be omitted?

